    "RoBERTa achieves 96.73% accuracy and 0.01 loss on the training set, maintaining 93.60% accuracy and 0.02 loss on the test set, outperforming the other models.",
    "DeBERTa closely follows, achieving 95.67% accuracy and 0.02 loss on the training set, with a test set accuracy of 94.00% and a 0.01 loss.",
    "Although BERT also shows significant The distilled models still exhibit lower accuracy and higher loss on the testing sets compared to the training sets.",
    "For example, BERT achieves 93.6% accuracy and 0.03 loss on the training set, while its accuracy slightly drops to 91.90%, and the loss increases to 0.05 on the test set.",
    "Similarly, RoBERTa's accuracy decreases from 96.73% on the training set to 93.60% on the test set, and its loss rises from 0.01 to 0.02."
